Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (LSCF) perovskite was studied as a possible cathode material for inter-mediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Synthesis, characterization, and electrochemical properties of bi-layered cathode films deposited on co-doped ceria

Sentencas: The LSCF material, prepared using the Pechini method, exhibited chemical compatibility with the Ce0.8Sm0.17La0.03O1.9 (LaSDC) electrolyte up to a temperature of 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis, characterization, and electrochemical properties of bi-layered cathode films deposited on co-doped ceria

Sentencas: The symmetrical LSCF/LaSDC/LSCF half-cell was studied through structural and morphological analyses.
Titulo: Synthesis, characterization, and electrochemical properties of bi-layered cathode films deposited on co-doped ceria

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of the spin coated and screen-printed LSCF thin and thick porous films on a dense LaSDC electrolyte were measured between 600-700 degrees C in air over.
Titulo: Synthesis, characterization, and electrochemical properties of bi-layered cathode films deposited on co-doped ceria

Sentencas: The electrical properties of a half-cell in air gave low ASR values, 0.032 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C and 0.077 Omega.cm(2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis, characterization, and electrochemical properties of bi-layered cathode films deposited on co-doped ceria

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3/Ce0.8Sm0.17La0.03O1.9 half-cell could potentially be used as good candidate for its application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Synthesis, characterization, and electrochemical properties of bi-layered cathode films deposited on co-doped ceria
